Package com.nrg948.autonomous

Annotation Interface AutonomousCommandGenerator

public @interface AutonomousCommandGenerator
Annotates a method that creates a Collection of LabelValue elements mapping the name to display in user interface elements like SendableChooser to a Command.

The method must conform to the following prototype: 

 
 public static Collection<LabelValue<String, Command>> name(Object... args);
The list of arguments passed to the Autonomous.getChooser(Object...) method will be passed to the annotated method. This is typically a single parameter of type RobotContainer but may be another type managing access to the subsystems or the list of subsystems themselves. All annotated methods must accept the same types and number of arguments.
